   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make the following checks monthly:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li platform="PxW WxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">With an appropriate rated measuring
instrument check:</p>
                  <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                     <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The battery voltage.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The DC voltage.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The system output voltage.</p>
                     </li>
                     <li class="- topic/li ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">The system output current.</p>
                     </li>
                  </ol>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Record any present alarms or incorrect operating status indications.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Reset any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b>. Make sure that the system operates correctly and no alarms
are indicated on the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Alarm panel</b>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Press and hold the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> to check that all LEDs on the front panel (alarm panel, mimic diagram
and common alarm) illuminate.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform required maintenance on the batteries,
see the section <xref href="#./CheckTheBatteries-95B05A30"
                           scope="local"
                           type="section"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section id="CheckTheBatteries-95B05A30"
               platform="PxW SDC"
               class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Monthly Battery Check</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Always
check the documentation from the original equipment manufacturer (OEM)
of the batteries for values, measurements and detailed instructions
for maintenance.</note>
            <note class="- topic/note ">The following steps are only general
recommendations and might not be relevant for all types of batteries
or might not reflect the full extent of the required maintenance.</note>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check the battery voltage at the battery terminal.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check all wet battery cells on the liquid level and refill
if necessary.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check the voltage of each individual cell.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
